
[1]bowline

   BOWLINE, n. A rope fastened near the middle of the leech or
   perpendicular edge of the square sails, by subordinate parts, called
   bridles, and used to keep the weather edge of the sail tight
   forward,when the ship is close hauled.bridles, are the ropes by which
   the bowline is fastened to the leech of the sail.
